<!--
  Sample links.xml — copy this file to the TOP LEVEL of your --source project
  folder (the same place io-devices.xml/events.xml/.stignore live) and rename
  it to "links.xml". See "Variable links (links.xml)" in README.md for the
  full rules.

  This is TwinCAT's OWN native <VarLinks> export/import format — the exact
  same schema the XAE IDE itself produces via "Export Variable Mapping" and
  reads back via "Import Variable Mapping". Applied in ONE bulk COM call
  (ITcSysManager.ConsumeMappingInfo) — the file's raw text is handed straight
  to TwinCAT, not reinterpreted by this tool.

  THE EASIEST WAY TO GET A REAL, CORRECT links.xml: link your %I/%Q
  variables to hardware once by hand in the TwinCAT IDE (or against a
  simulated target), then run:
      beckhoffAutomationInterface.exe --source <path> --dest <path> --export-links
  which writes the current mapping here via ITcSysManager.ProduceMappingInfo
  — the same thing "Export Variable Mapping" does. Hand-authoring entries
  (as below) is also fine for simple, top-level GVL/PROGRAM variables.

  Schema — CONFIRMED against a live TwinCAT 3.1 install (2026-07-15): this is
  exactly what ProduceMappingInfo/ConsumeMappingInfo produce and accept here,
  round-trip verified end to end (linked, built cleanly, BUILD PASSED):
    <OwnerA Name="TIPC^<Plc>^<Plc> Instance">
      -- ONE PLC instance per OwnerA — both directions (inputs AND outputs)
         under the same OwnerA, no separate Type attribute needed.
      <OwnerB Name="TIID^<Device>^<Coupler>^<Terminal>">
        -- one IO box/device/terminal, addressed as raw TIID^... same as
           io-devices.xml's <Links> IoChannel (minus the trailing "^Channel N^Input|Output").
        <Link VarA="PlcTask Inputs|Outputs^<Gvl/Program>.<var>" VarB="<Entry>" />
        -- VarA is relative to OwnerA's Name, with the "PlcTask Inputs"/
           "PlcTask Outputs" group folded directly into it (joined by '^') —
           no separate GrpA attribute. VarB is relative to OwnerB's Name.
      </OwnerB>
    </OwnerA>

  A richer variant also exists in the wild (seen in a real reference
  project's own "Instance Mappings.xml" export, and in Beckhoff's official
  CodeGenerationDemo sample): OwnerA with separate Prefix/Type attributes and
  Link with a separate GrpA (plus TypeA/InOutA/ParentTypeA/GuidA metadata).
  This tool's own --check-links parses both shapes, but ONLY the shape above
  was confirmed to actually apply via ConsumeMappingInfo in live testing —
  the richer shape was tried first and silently applied nothing (no COM
  exception, but an --export-links round-trip came back empty). If you
  hand-author entries, use the shape below; if in doubt, always prefer
  --export-links over hand-authoring.
-->
<VarLinks>
	<OwnerA Name="TIPC^Shark^Shark Instance">
		<OwnerB Name="TIID^Device 1 (EtherCAT)^Term 1 (EK1100)^Term 2 (EL1008)">
			<Link VarA="PlcTask Inputs^GVL_Shark.bMotorRunSensor" VarB="Channel 1^Input" />
		</OwnerB>
		<OwnerB Name="TIID^Device 1 (EtherCAT)^Term 1 (EK1100)^Term 3 (EL2008)">
			<Link VarA="PlcTask Outputs^GVL_Shark.bMotorEnableOutput" VarB="Channel 1^Output" />
		</OwnerB>
	</OwnerA>
</VarLinks>
